{
  "text": "The halo sign is not exclusive of TA and has been observed in other vessels affected by GCA like vertebral, occipital, or axillary arteries. However, ultrasound diagnosis in vessels other than the TA is more difficult and positive findings are less frequent. [CITATION_1] We report 5 cases attended in our neurology department in the last 2 years in which vertebral artery (VA) halo sign was the clue for the early diagnosis of GCA as the primary cause of brain infarction.",
